UID:783d9f41-ddbb-4768-b44e-e3aaaa822536@travel-concierge
DESCRIPTION:**Day 1**\n- 07:30 🍳 Breakfast: Anokhi Cafe — try their s
 ignature pancakes\, ~₹250/person\n- 09:30 🏛️ Morning: City Palace (
 open 09:30–17:30\, entry ₹200) — a majestic blend of Rajput and Mugh
 al architecture\, showcasing the rich history of Jaipur\n  → Transport: 
 Hire a shared taxi (₹500\, 30 minutes) from the airport for the group\n-
  13:00 🍽️ Lunch: Chokhi Dhani — recommended: traditional Rajasthani
  thali\, ~₹400/person\n- 15:00 🎭 Afternoon: Jantar Mantar (open 09:30
 –16:30\, entry ₹50) — an ancient astronomical observatory with the w
 orld's largest stone sundial\n  → Transport: Walk from City Palace (10 m
 inutes)\n- 19:00 🌅 Sunset: Nahargarh Fort — watch the sunset over the
  city from this historic fort\n- 20:00 🍷 Dinner: Rawat Mishthan Bhandar
  — must-try: their famous dal baati churma\, ~₹300/person\n- 💡 Loca
 l tip: Explore the local bazaars\, like Bapu Bazaar\, for authentic Rajast
 hani handicrafts and souvenirs\n- ☔ Indoor backup: Visit the Albert Hall
  Museum (open 09:30–17:30) to learn about Jaipur's history and culture\n
 - 👥 Group tip: Book a shared taxi or minivan for the day to ensure conv
 enient and cost-effective transportation for the group
END:VEVENT
