 tiful white marble temple dedicated to Lord Vishnu\n  → Transport: Take 
 a shared auto-rickshaw (₹100\, 20 minutes) for the group\n- 13:00 🍽
 ️ Lunch: Lakshmi Mishtan Bhandar — recommended: their veg thali\, ~₹
 300/person\n- 15:00 🎭 Afternoon: Rajasthali (open 10:00–19:00\, entry
  ₹50) — a handicraft village showcasing traditional Rajasthani crafts\
 n  → Transport: Drive to Rajasthali (30 minutes)\n- 19:00 🌅 Sunset: C
 entral Park — enjoy the scenic views of the city from this well-maintain
 ed park\n- 20:00 🍷 Dinner: Natraj — must-try: their veg biryani\, ~
 ₹250/person\n- 💡 Local tip: Attend a traditional Rajasthani folk danc
 e performance at a local venue\n- ☔ Indoor backup: Visit the Entertainme
 nt Paradise (open 11:00–23:00) for some indoor fun and games\n- 👥 Gro
 up tip: Book a private room at a local restaurant for dinner to ensure a c
 omfortable and intimate experience for the group
